<HEAD>Transcript of Bentsen's Statement On Becoming Dukakis' Running
Mate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a transcript of Texas Sen. Lloyd Bentsen's
statement Tuesday following Michael Dukakis' selection of Bentsen
as his running mate.
   Well, Mike, I can tell this campaign is already beginning to
heat up.
   Joining this campaign as the vice presidential candidate is not
just an honor, but I think it's a great opportunity to make a
difference for America. The Massachusetts and the Texas axis was
good for the country and good for the Democratic Party in 1960 and
it's going to be a real winner in November of '88.
   Michael Dukakis, the son of immigrant parents, a man whose going
to grow up to be president of the most powerful and prosperous
nation in the world, a man whose living out his parents' dreams,
but once that dream of reality for all Americans, a reality of
jobs, education, health care, these are the things Michael Dukakis
is for. And what I'm impressed with is how he reaches out to the
rest of the country.
   You got a situation in the economy today where it's like a piece
of Swiss cheese with holes in it. Other parts of this economy not
doing as well as the two coasts. But choosing a representative from
that part of the country, once that kind of imput, an inclusive
campaign that reaches out across America, that's what Michael
Dukakis has done and it's going to be a winner.
   Michael Dukakis is a man who didn't turn Massachusetts around
with taxes and spending, but he turned it around with some virtues
that we understand through the Southwest and the South. The virtues
of hard work, the entrepreneurial spirit, integrity and he brought
effective management of the taxpayers' dollar to a new high, and
I'm impressed with that kind of record and so is the country.
   The fact that he's taken a senator from Texas, a senator from
the South, shows that we're going to fight for every state in the
union and we're going all out to win.
   I'm delighted to be back in a state where my great-great-uncle
was a senator from Massachusetts and became vice president of the
United States of America and we're out to duplicate that record
today. Thank you Mike.
</TEXT>
