<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Greece-Terrorism     07-13 0268</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Greece-Terrorism,0274</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cruise Ship Attack Latest In Terrorist Attacks Involving Greece</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Greece-Ship Attack, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The attack aboard a Greek cruise ship was
one of the bloodiest terrorist actions involving Greece in the past
three years. Following are some of the major acts of terrorism
since 1985.
   _June 28, 1988: Capt. William E. Nordeen, a U.S. defense
attache, killed in a car-bomb blast in an Athens suburb. A
left-wing terrorist group, calling itself November 17, claimed
responsibility. November 17 terrorists have been blamed for 12
political assassinations in 13 years, including the deaths of three
Americans. None of its members has been arrested.
   _Aug. 10, 1987: A car bomb exploded next to a busload of
American servicemen in a seaside suburb of Athens, wounding 11
people. November 17 said it was responsible.
   _April 24, 1987: A bomb exploded in front of a van carrying U.S.
servicemen in Athens and 18 were wounded. November 17 said its
members made the attack.
   _April 2, 1986: An explosion ripped a hole in the fuselage of a
Trans World Airlines jetliner flying over southern Greece. Four
Americans, including a mother, her daughter and infant
grandaughter, perished in the blast.
   _Nov. 24, 1985: A Cairo-bound Egyptair passenger jet was
hijacked shortly after leaving Athens. It was diverted to Malta,
where 60 people were killed when Egyptian commandos assaulted the
plane.
   _June 14, 1985: A TWA jet flying from Athens to Rome is hijacked
soon after takeoff. One American, a U.S. Navy diver, was killed and
38 people were held hostage 17 days before being released in
Beirut, Lebanon.
</TEXT>
