<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets,0194</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Stocks and Dollar Decline</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices dropped slightly on the Tokyo Stock
Exchange today, and the dollar lost ground against the Japanese yen.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, a 113.85-point
winner Tuesday, shed 79.74 points, or 0.28 percent, to close the
day's trading at 28,020.10 points.
   The dollar finished at 132.47 yen, down 0.23 yen from Tuesday's
132.70 yen close. It opened at 132.33 yen and traded mainly between
132.27 yen and 132.58 yen during the day.
   Traders said the stock market opened in a bullish mood but
started falling in midmorning trading.
   ``I don't see an outstanding factor which caused the decline,''
said a trader at a major securities firm, speaking on condition of
anonymity. ``Investors are sidelined until the release of the trade
figures in the United States at the end of the week.''
   The U.S. Commerce Department is due to release a trade report
for the month of May on Friday.
   Another trader, who also spoke privately, said the fall of share
prices for no particular reason indicates that the market may have
hit its ceiling.
</TEXT>
