distressed many officers.
   Cannatella refused to rule out a job action during the
convention.
   Barthelemy refused to say how the city would deal with a police
job action during the convention Aug. 15-18, although about 60
Louisiana State Police troopers were brought in to work alongside
city police who worked Monday.
   State police are already planning to send about 130 troopers and
investigators to New Orleans for the convention.
