<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Roof Collapse-Victim,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Boy May Lose Kidneys Due to Roof Collapse</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GALVESTON, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 9-year-old trapped for 20 hours in the
rubble of a collapsed department store is in critical condition
with kidney problems, doctors said.
   Physicians at the University of Texas Medical Branch said that
toxins from dead muscle tissue apparently destroyed Jorge Mena's
ability to cleanse his blood and that the boy from Merida, Mexico,
may lose use of his kideys.
   The Amigo Store in Brownsville collapsed during heavy rain
Friday, killing 14 people and injuring at least 47. Investigators
have not determined the cause.
   ``He complains the whole time he is in the (hyperbaric)
chamber,'' said Dr. John Mader, who is overseeing the boy's
high-pressure oxygen treatments. ``But that's good because he's a
fighter, and that is what it takes.''
   Jorge's mother remained hospitalized in Brownsville, and a
15-year-old sister died in the accident, authorities said.
