<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Chippendales     07-13 0209</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Chippendales,0214</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Retransmitting to fix cycle designator</HEAD>
<HEAD>Fire Department Revokes Chippendales Fire Permit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chippendales nightclub, with its all-male
dance revue for women, has been packing 'em in. So much so that the
Fire Department has ordered it closed next month for repeated
instances of overcrowding.
   The department notified Chippendales Tuesday that it has revoked
the establishment's fire permit and given it until Aug. 4 to close
because of ``repeated and flagrant disregard of the fire code,''
said Battalion Chief Dean Cathey.
   ``We're not talking about five to 10 people,'' Cathey said. The
club has a capacity of 299, but as many as 576 people have been
jammed inside, he said.
   Over the past five years, Chippendales has been cited 14 times
for overcrowding and has received fines totaling $14,300 and
probation adding up of 36 months, Cathey said.
   Manager Steve Banerjee said his club is being targeted because
of the nature of its entertainment, which features gyrating,
scantily-clad men. He said he has hired attorney Melvin Belli to
sue the Fire Department.
   ``I'm sure if we provided entertainment for men, we wouldn't be
having this trouble,'' he said.
   Cathey denied any bias. ``If they're not breaking the law, they
won't be cited,'' he said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
