<1ST_LINE>r a PM-MTVNominations     07-13 0204</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-MTV Nominations,0209</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Nominations for 1988 Music Video Awards Announced</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Videos by the Australian group INXS and
former Beatle George Harrison were among the top nominees for this
year's MTV Music Video Awards.
   Musical clips by INXS, a high-energy pop group led by singer
Michael Hutchence, earned eight nominations, including best video
and best group video, for ``Need You Tonight-Mediate.''
   The ``When We Was Fab'' video from Harrison, recalling his days
as a Beatle, earned best video and best concept video nominations.
   Clips from the Irish group U2 earned six nominations, including
two in the best video category for ``Where the Streets Have No
Name'' and ``I Still Haven't Found What I'm Looking For.'' The two
videos also were nominated in the best concept category.
   Other multiple nominees included three for videos by George
Michael and four for videos by Bruce Springsteen.
   The nominees in 15 categories were announced during a breakfast
news conference Tuesday. The MTV Music Video Awards, the fifth
sponsored by MTV, will be broadcast live on the MTV cable network
from the Universal Amphitheater Sept. 7.
   Nominees were selected by representatives of the music video
business, including record executives, attorneys, journalists,
producers, agents and artists.
</TEXT>
