<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Libya-Bomb     07-13 0071</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Libya-Bomb,0072</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>World War II Bomb Explodes In Libya, Killing 8</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A World War II bomb buried in a field in northern
Libya blew up, killing a family of eight, the official Libyan news
agency said Wednesday.
   JANA, monitored in Rome, said the 650-pound bomb exploded
Saturday in Ban al-Zaytun, 12 miles east of the city of Tubruq.
   It did not say how the blast was triggered.
</TEXT>
