<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--China-Heat     07-13 0144</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--China-Heat,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rain Breaks Heat Wave In Eastern China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nanking residents set off firecrackers to welcome
a rainstorm that broke a 10-day heat wave in which 83 people died,
an official report said Wednesday.
   Torrential rains fell for 45 minutes Tuesday night in the
eastern city, causing the temperature to fall from 102 to 95, the
Xinhua News Agency said.
   People rushed into the streets and let off firecrackers in
celebration, the report said. It said forecasters predicted more
rain.
   Xinhua said Monday that 83 people had died and 1,500 were
hospitalized because of the heat, most of them elderly.
   Temperatures had hovered from 100 to 102 since July 2 in what
Xinhua called the third-worst heat wave since 1905.
   It did not say when the worst heat wave occurred. Nanking
typically has hot summers, earning it the nickname ``furnace.''
</TEXT>
