<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Italy-Mafia     07-13 0137</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Italy-Mafia,0140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mafia Boss Shot To Death In Reputed Settlement of Accounts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALERMO, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A convicted Mafia boss was ambushed and
shot to death near this Sicilian capital in what police described
as a settlement of accounts between rival gangs.
   Pietro Messicati Vitale, 41, was hit by at least five shots of a
lupara _ the sawed-off shotgun traditionally used by the Mafia _ as
he rode a motorcycle Tuesday to his vacation villa looking out on
Capo Zafferano Bay.
   Messicati Vitale was arrested in 1985 and later sentenced to
eight years in prison after being convicted on charges of criminal
association. The prosecution described him as the boss of a drug
trafficking ring.
   He was released a month ago because of a procedural error in his
trial and was awaiting a second trial.
</TEXT>
