<HEAD>Guerrillas Attack Festival In Mozambique, Kill 16</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAPUTO, Mozambique (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Guerrillas attacked revelers at a
festival in Mozambique's second largest city, killing 16 people and
injuring 72, the national news agency said.
   AIM said in a dispatch Tuesday that it was the first large-scale
attack by the Mozambique National Resistance on residents of Beira,
a port on the Indian Ocean coast.
   AIM said about 50 guerrillas attacked Beira's suburb of
Inhamizua late Saturday night while residents were dancing and
singing at a neighborhood fair.
   The guerrillas have been waging a hit-and-run insurgency since
1977 that has left hundreds of thousands of people homeless and in
need of food aid.
