<DATELINE>BRESCIA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The chauffeur for Princess Caroline of
Monaco was indicted Wednesday on drug trafficking charges, the
Italian news agency ANSA reported.
   The driver, Antonino Barca, was accused by Investigating
Magistrate Roberto di Martino of running drugs between Italy and
Spain, the agency reported. Twelve other people also were indicted,
most on charges of receiving shipments of hashish, ANSA said.
   Monaco extradited Barca to Italy two months ago and he is free
pending trial, according to the agency. No date was set for the
proceedings.
