<HEAD>Suspected East German Spy Arrested In Bavaria</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNICH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man suspected of being an East
German spy was arrested after crossing from East Germany into
Bavaria posing as a hiker, officials said Wednesday.
   The unidentified 29-year-old man carried a false passport
bearing the name of a living West German man, said Bavarian state
police.
   After interrogation by police, the suspect admitted he was a
citizen of East Germany, officials said.
   The man was arrested June 16 near the East German border at
Maroldsweisach, in northern Bavaria, officials said.
   The arrest was not immediately announced so the investigation
would not be jeopardized, police said.
   Police did not say what kind of espionage the East German was
allegedly assigned to undertake in West Germany.
