<NOTE>For Release Weekend Editions, July 22-24, and Thereafter</NOTE>
<HEAD>Melody Thomas Scott Stars in No. 1 Daytime Soap Opera</HEAD>
<NOTE>With LaserPhoto</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By JERRY BUCK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Melody Thomas Scott says that in nine years
on CBS' ``The Young and the Restless'' her character has grown up
and undergone changes.
   ``When I began, Nikki was very poor, lower-class and troubled,''
she said. ``She's still troubled, but now she's rich.''
   Scott also grew up on the show. Three years ago she married the
executive producer, Edward Scott, and they are expecting their
first child at Thanksgiving.
   Although she was a teen-ager when she began the daytime serial,
she was already a veteran performer. She had worked with Clint
Eastwood twice as well as Kirk Douglas, John Wayne and Geraldine
Page.
   Her character, Nikki Reed Newman, has also packed a lot of
living into her years on ``The Young and the Restless.''
   ``She's gone through many marriages, many phases,'' said Scott.
``She's been a stripper, a model, a member of a cult and chased by
a psychotic killer. In my first story on the show my father tried
to rape me. I don't think that went over well with the audience. I
hit him over the head, he died and that was the end of that.
   ``Now I'm married to the Howard Hughes of Genoa City. It's not a
happy marriage. We had a storybook romance and wedding. My wedding
gown cost $25,000. It was wonderful for a while. We still live
together, but we live separate lives. Now that I'm pregnant I'm
hoping he will change his mind.''
   Her husband on the show is Victor Newman, played by Eric Braeden.
   ``I'm very happy with the show,'' said Scott. ``In my opinion
it's the best medium for an actress who wants to have a family. The
hours for a prime-time show are horrendous. I wouldn't want to be
running around the world on location. I usually don't go in until
noon. I'm usually through by 6 o'clock. It works out very good for
me.''
   Although the soap has about 25 regular characters, the main
storyline follows Nikki and her husband. The story began about 2{
years ago when ``The Young and the Restless'' began to challenge
ABC's ``General Hospital'' for the ratings leadership among the
daytime serials. In the current season, it is ranking first in the
Nielsen daytime ratings.
   Scott was born in Los Angeles and started her career at age 3 as
one of ``The Meglin Kiddies.'' Ethel Meglin, who recently died, had
started such other performers as Shirley Temple and Judy Garland.
The Meglin group put on musical performances around California.
   ``I was raised by my grandmother, who always talked about Jane
Withers,'' she said. ``She was one of my idols.'' Withers, probably
best known to current generations for her ``Josephine the Plumber''
commercials several years ago, was a major child star.
   Scott also appeared in commercials and did guest spots on such
shows as ``My Three Sons'' and ``Ironside.'' At 8, she played Tippi
Hedren's daughter in ``Marnie.'' She was a regular on ``The Tammy
Grimes Show.''
   ``I never thought much about doing the shows,'' she said. ``When
you're that young you don't think about it. I thought all kids did
it.''
   When she was in junior high school she read in a trade paper
that director Don Siegel was looking for ``a chubby little girl''
to appear with Clint Eastwood and Geraldine Page in ``The
Beguiled.'' She stuffed herself to gain weight, then rented a Civil
War costume and auditioned for Siegel. She got the role, and later
when Siegel directed Eastwood in ``Dirty Harry'' he remembered her
and put her in the movie.
   She was also in ``Posse'' with Kirk Douglas and such TV movies
and miniseries as ``Studs Lonigan,'' ``Moviola'' and ``Secrets.''
She had a recurring role on ``The Waltons.''
   Scott appeared with John Wayne in his last movie, ``The
Shootist.''
   ``I played the sweet little girl in that,'' she said. ``I had a
scene with John Wayne on a streetcar. It was a thrill to do that.''
   She met her husband while doing ``The Young and the Restless.''
   ``He's been producer about 12 or 13 years,'' she said. ``For
many years we had just a working relationship. Then we became
friends and we got married three years ago.''
   She has a 5-year-old daughter, Alexandra, from an earlier
marriage, and her husband has a 15-year-old daughter, Jennifer.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Weekend Editions, July 23-24</NOTE>
