higher interest rates. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials fell
18.67 points to 2,092.64.
   The dollar slipped against most major currencies. Gold prices
were mixed.
   Bond prices declined on inflation concerns and the weaker dollar.
   Grain and soybean futures closed moderately higher in cautious
trading ahead of an eagerly awaited government crop report.
