<1ST_LINE>u f BC-BritainStocks 1stLd-Writethru   07-13 0173</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0179</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Shares Up 12.8 Points</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New throughout.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stocks rose in light trading on London's Stock
Exchange Wednesday, as investors waited for a barrage of U.S. and
British economic reports due later in the week.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index ended 12.8
points, or 0.7 percent, higher at 1,871.3.
   Trading volume was 430.8 million shares, compared with Tuesday's
398 million shares.
   Traders said a strong opening on Wall Street gave the London
market a boost.
   But the impending economic reports kept many potential
participants sidelined, dealers said.
   The most crucial report was considered the U.S. trade report,
which is scheduled for release Friday.
   The U.S. merchandise trade deficit is widely expected to have
grown to between $11 billion and $12 billion in May from April's
$9.9 billion.
   The market expects another round of global interest rate hikes,
but the authorities must first see the outcome of the trade figures
before raising rates, said Glenn Davies, an equities analyst with
CL-Alexanders Laing Cruickshank Ltd.
</TEXT>
