<HEAD>With AM-Business Climate Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the rankings of states in the ninth
annual ``Manufacturing Climates Study'' conducted by the accounting
firm of Grant Thornton.
   For the first time since the study was conducted, states were
divided into categories of high- or low-manufacturing intensity. To
be ranked among the high-intensity group, total employment in
manufacturing in the state in 1987 must have exceeded the national
average of 17 percent or manufacturing shipments must have exceeded
the national average in dollar terms.
</TEXT>
