<DATELINE>SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hewlett-Packard Co., responding to an
Apple Computer Inc. copyright infringement suit, countersued in
federal court Wednesday alleging unfair business practices and
antitrust violations by Apple.
   Hewlett-Packard, based in Palo Alto, also denied all of Apple's
allegations and asked the U.S. District Court in San Jose to
invalidate Apple's copyrights in the case and dismiss its suit
against Hewlett-Packard.
   ``HP is confident the court will agree Apple's suit has no
