<1ST_LINE>u f AM-Japan-Markets 1stLd-Writethru f0288 07-13 0142</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0288,0145</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Stocks Lower, Dollar Higher In Tokyo Morning Trading</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New throughout to UPDATE with morning stock closing,
comments. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were lower following a strong opening
Thursday morning, while the U.S. dollar gained slightly against the
Japanese yen.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected shares closed the
morning session at 27,968.40, down 51.70 points from Wednesday's
close, after rising by more than 107 points in heavy activity
during the first 15 minutes of trading.
   Traders said the market was dominated by speculative, short-term
trading ahead of the U.S. trade figures for May, due to be released
Friday in Washington.
   In foreign exchange, the dollar opened at 132.75 yen, up 0.28
yen from Wednesday's finish, and later fluctuated between 132.75
yen and 132.85 yen in relatively active morning trading, dealers
said.
